<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>7834</id>
    <title>user logged into facebook is not logged into canvas application on IE</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">Hi_</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">This is an issue which occurs on IE and Safari_ it does not occur on Firefox.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">If you login to facebook as normal and then browse to the apps page_ the application which is sitting embedded in the canvas is not passed the logged in status and hence is not authenticated.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Here are the steps to reproduce.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">1 Browse to http://www.facebook.com and login with your username and password.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.3">2 Browse to http://apps.facebook.com/christmas_carol_test/</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.4">3 Select a language_ say_ English and click  Continue</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.5">4 You will see a message which says  authenticated: False .</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">If you repeat the steps above on Firefox_ it appears as authenticated: True.</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">It seems like IE and Safari are not allowing the authentication to take place in the iframe.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Is there a solution / work around for this?</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Thank You_</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Keith.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
